My baby has turned four months old today😍
I wouldn’t say time just flied, instead  these 4 months seemed like F-O-U-R long years to me- filled with roller coaster of emotions!
Seeing him grow up each day is the most beautiful thing to look forward to.
Each day we get to see his new milestones, new expressions, new achievements- can never express the amount of happiness it brings to us.
Mihaan- you’re just not a part of our lives, you’re our life❤️
Wishing you more love and happiness your way🥰

latestPosts.caption:
18.02.2022- That day😍Remember each & every moment and feeling that I was going through. It was a planned surgery and I was shit scared. If you don’t know me closely, let me tell you that nothing scares me more than an injection. The thought of surgery didn’t let me sleep entire last night. That morning, we left for the hospital and I was getting ready for it- both physically and mentally. I was shivering with fear when I was taken inside. Anaesthesiologist and my Gynac (acquainted with my fear all these months) kept assuring me. 
And those 12 minutes were the longest T-W-E-L-V-E minutes of my life! Kept asking them impatiently every 10 seconds “how long”? 
And finally heard from them “ladka hai” followed by my baby’s cry and there I saw him- the most beautiful, blissful and amazing moment of my life so far. I’m sure every mother can relate with this. 
The surprising part was that I didn’t go through any pain at all- neither the injection’s nor the incision pain later- not sure if I turned stronger while becoming a mother or was it the excitement of motherhood subsiding all the pain. 
Well, sharing glimpses of Mihaan’s initial pictures when he was busy sleeping while I was enjoying myself on Cloud nine😇🥰
.
.
.
.
.

What makes a show stimulating:
⚠️Dancing objects
⚠️Vibrant colours
⚠️Intensity of sound effects
⚠️Rapid screen change

Some common behavioural issues that kids face with excessive screentime or watching overstimulating shows:
🔺Screentime is known to cause speech delay in kids too
🔺Affects brain development 
🔺Chronic neck & back pain
🔺Depression and anxiety 
🔺Can cause obesity
🔺Reduced interest in playing with other kids

(Read pointers in pinned comments👇🏻)

📢This post is not to create any pressure or guilt but to help parents who are willing to reduce or eliminate screentime but unable to do so.
Hope this helps❤️

latestPosts.caption:
I’m sure it happens with most of us that after kids, there’s little to no romance in our lives anymore! Could be because of multiple reasons, maybe stress or arguments over parenting styles but don’t you think we parents must team up together and not be competitive about it!
Also, as we grow up, kids take over their own lives and maybe settle down away from us but what we will always have beside us, is each other, now and forever!
So why not cherish this relationship even more and put in some conscious efforts to make each other feel special and loved🫶🏻

Share this with your partner and remind them how much you love them❤️

Btw, there’s a reason why I’ve picked this song. It was the first ever song that my husband dedicated to me and we had also danced on this on our Sangeet night so it’s always special❤️

Do you struggle with excessive screentime for your toddlers?
Here are 75 ways to engage your toddler without screentime.

🔷25 activities for your toddlers to keep them screen-free:
1.Paste dot stickers on balloon
2.Put Q tips in steel strainer
3.Sensory play tub
4.Take out Rubber bands using a straw
5.Pompoms drop through tunnel
6.Paste pitballs on tape
7.Pouring water from one cup to another
8.Painting
9.Match real veggies with flashcards
10.Match lids with containers
11.Match socks with another pair
12.Problem solving activity (puzzles; blocks etc)
13.Sieving pompoms from water 
14.Pompoms colour sorting in muffin tray
15.Rescue pompoms from the whisk
16.Sort legumes in a bowl
17.Walking on rice
18.Hiding toys in rice
19.Transferring rice to small containers
20.Pouring rice through a funnel
21.Paper tunnel car activity 
22.Stick animal figurines on cellotape
23.Rescue animal figurines from foil paper (wrap animal figurines in foil papers and then encourage them to rescue)
24.Playdough stamping (using key; animal)
25.Egg smashing activity 

🔶25 Life skills to teach your toddler:
1. Put toys in the basket
2. Put books on the shelf
3. Put away shoes 
4. Throw away diapers 
5. Help clean up spills
6. Put their utensils in sink
7. Put their clothes in the machine
8. Wipe down their table after meals
9. Drinking from an open cup
10. Using a straw
11. Eating with a spoon
12. Make an easy snack
13. Trashing things
14. How to use scissors
15. Learn to use glue & paper
16. Water plants using a spray
17. Fold their laundry
18. Feed pets
19. Help younger siblings 
20. Pick out clothes for the week
21. Get/pour their own water
22. Tidy up their room
23. Make their bed
24. Take off dirty bedding
25. Getting backpack ready for school
